## ğŸ”— API Testing in Playwright

Playwright includes **built-in API testing support**, allowing testers to:

- Send HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Validate response status codes and payloads
- Perform backend validation before or after UI actions

This enables **end-to-end testing combining UI and API** in a single test flow.

---

## â³ Automatic Waiting (Auto-Wait)

One of Playwrightâ€™s strongest features is **automatic waiting**.

Playwright automatically waits for:
- Elements to be visible
- Elements to be enabled
- Network calls to complete
- Page navigation to finish

This **reduces flaky tests** and removes the need for manual waits.

